==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Chauffeur
<hw>Chauf`feur"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., lit.,
stoker.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> [<pluf>pl.</pluf>] <fld>(F. Hist.)</fld>
<def>Brigands in bands, who, about 1793, pillaged, burned, and killed in
parts of France; -- so called because they used to burn the feet of
their victims to extort money.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who manages the running of an automobile or
limousine; esp., the paid operator of a motor vehicle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chauffeuse</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
